rComments: Terrible organization. Incredibly rude TAs. Terrible course layout, based only on tests with poor marking schemes. Would not recommend if the course was not mandatory.
Most useless lecture I've ever attended you are better off just practicing the problems on your own.

Idk what these other reviewers are talking about his lectures are pretty interesting. Also you should have figured out by now that there will be things you have to learn yourself you're already third year lol

If you know nothing about finance, do go to lectures because he starts from very basics on each topic; otherwise, he may seem to over explain basic concepts. If you know basics, skip lectures, instead every problem set & practice! That's because tests are not hard, but very complex cascade-style questions. Maintain a clear head and you'd be ok
U should really check his sides. It's more like a boring 80's newspaper instead of a lecture note.

Makes a really dry topic (accounting and finance) interesting and relevant to engineering. Good explanations, good organization, and more then willing to answer questions after class, though as he is the CFO for something, he might be hard to reach for office hours. Tests are tough though, but as a 4th year ECE student, this should not surpris you.
Not helpful at all
Terrible prof, poor explanation and slides, irresponsible and he refuses to explain questions on previous tests.

Nice guy and great speaker but you don't learn much from his lectures. The only way to benefit would be to have in-depth knowledge of economic concepts beforehand. I like to think that it isn't his fault, it's more due to the nature of the material itself.
Useless lecture, over explain everything. Does not care about his student

This is a very formula-oriented course so it's more worthwhile to skip lectures and read the book, than to hear him over-explain everything at a slow pace. Make sure to do EVERY recommended problem set before a quiz or you'll regret it. Provided you commit yourself to reading the book, skipping his lectures raises your chances of a good grade.

What the prof said is so vague. JRE30, on the other hand is more up to date, and actually useful. Whatever he said in the class WILL NOT appear on the quiz or exam!! This is one of the classes that uoft should consider to be removed.
Honestly one of the most interesting lecturers at U of T. I've never fallen asleep in his classes
Very friendly but classes are completely useless.
His moustache has its own personality
He doesn't care about the students, very irresponsible.

This professor spends most of the lecture going over concepts and not with test materials. If you want to do well in the course, going to the tutorials would be more helpful since the material covered there are the ones tested. The professor isn't very helpful either since he doesn't even allow for an office hour to discuss things with students.
Knows what he's talking about, but at times an inconsiderate ass.
Easily the best and most interesting lecturer I have ever had. Actually made economics my favourite course this semester. Fills his lectures with real life, interesting examples. Very helpful guy.
He's awesome, rocks at teaching and really knows his stuff

he teaches eco to engineers and makes sure people understand and is willing to answer any question any time during class and likes to leak out questions to quizes if people skip his class for other midterms or quizes
